    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is organized into five thematic sections (Nile, Customs, Gods, Kings, Wonders) accessible via a top navigation bar. This non-linear structure allows users to explore topics of interest freely, rather than following the book's narrative sequentially. The core interaction is a horizontal timeline of kings, making the dense historical information digestible and engaging. A bar chart compares reign lengths for a quantitative overview. This design prioritizes user-driven exploration and thematic understanding over a simple text summary. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 1. Kings' Reigns: Goal: Compare historical periods. Viz: Horizontal Bar Chart (Chart.js/Canvas). Interaction: Tooltips on hover. Justification: Provides a quick visual comparison of the duration and impact of key rulers. 2. Timeline of Kings: Goal: Organize chronology. Method: Interactive HTML/CSS timeline. Interaction: Clicking a king's name reveals a detailed info card (JS). Justification: Breaks down the long, complex list of monarchs into manageable, explorable segments. 3. Egyptian Customs: Goal: Inform/Organize. Method: Grid of info cards (HTML/Tailwind). Interaction: Simple, clear presentation. Justification: Highlights the unique cultural aspects Herodotus noted in an easily scannable format. NO SVG/Mermaid used. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
